<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎮 M000 Pre-Lesson — Get Comfy in Minecraft</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Moving &amp; Building · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<hr />
<p>This is a warm-up <strong>before Lesson 1</strong>. No coding yet. The goal is to get comfortable playing Minecraft — moving around and placing blocks — so Lesson 1 feels easy. Open your Minecraft world and have fun.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Move Around 🎮</h2>
<p>Get into your world and try each move. Tick the box when you can do it.</p>
<ul>
<li>☐ Walk forward, back, left, and right</li>
<li>☐ Look around by moving the mouse</li>
<li>☐ Jump</li>
<li>☐ Look up at the sky, then down at the ground</li>
<li>☐ Walk up onto a hill or a block</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>On a computer: walk with <strong>W A S D</strong>, look with the <strong>mouse</strong>, jump with the <strong>space bar</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Which move was the trickiest? Write one sentence.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Break and Place Blocks 🧱</h2>
<p>Now change the world a little. Tick each one.</p>
<ul>
<li>☐ Break one block (dig it away)</li>
<li>☐ Place one block</li>
<li>☐ Open your inventory and pick a new kind of block</li>
<li>☐ Build a small tower 3 blocks tall</li>
<li>☐ Break your tower back down</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Which block did you like the most? Write one sentence.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Build a House 🏠</h2>
<p>Now build a small house by hand. Any size is fine — it does not need to be perfect. Your house needs <strong>4 things</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>☐ Four walls</li>
<li>☐ A door you can walk through</li>
<li>☐ Two windows (use glass, or leave two holes)</li>
<li>☐ A roof on top</li>
</ul>
<p>Take your time and try different blocks.</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me About Your House 📸</h2>
<p>Send a photo of your finished house to your teacher. Then finish these sentences — write 3 or 4.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My house is made of …</p>
<p>The door is on the …</p>
<p>My favourite part is …</p>
<p>The hardest part was …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Show Me Around 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a short video walking around your house. Talk like you are showing a friend. Try to use these words: <strong>walls</strong>, <strong>door</strong>, <strong>window</strong>, <strong>roof</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Walk up to your house.</li>
<li>Show the door and walk inside.</li>
<li>Point to the windows and the roof.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your house video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
